Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm chunks.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the tomatoes, a drizzle of @olive oil{}, half the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

Remove the stems from the @portobello mushrooms{2} (but leave the mushrooms whole). Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

Fry the mushrooms until golden brown, ~{4-5%minutes}, then turn over and cook for a further ~{4-5%minutes}.

Transfer the mushrooms, stem-side up, to a baking tray. Sprinkle over the cheese and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the cheese has melted, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Pop the (now) empty #frying pan{} back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Stir through the @fig jam{40%g} and remaining @balsamic vinegar{12%ml}. Cook until caramelised and sticky, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

When the mushrooms and chips are almost ready, halve the @burger buns{2}.

Pop the buns onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spread the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} over the bun lids.

Top the bun bases with the cheesy mushrooms, sticky onions and some @wild rocket{20%g}, then sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Add the remaining @wild rocket{20%g} to the bowl of tomatoes and toss to combine.

Serve your mushroom burgers with the fries and salad alongside. Enjoy!